The South African Weather Service says nights will be especially cold with temperatures dropping below zero. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng residents are in for another chilly day on Wednesday. A cold front hit Gauteng on Monday and is expected to last until the end of the week. The South African Weather Service says nights will be especially cold with temperatures dropping below zero. Forecaster Puseletso Mofokeng explains: “The weather will continue to be cold during the morning and during the day. In fact, I think we will get some relief on Friday.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)